rankings.summary: QB cheat code plus top-end anchors keeps you atop despite a 1-1 start.

key_players.name: Patrick Mahomes
key_players.note: Still the weekly floor/ceiling king in SF; pairing him with Herbert is just rude.

key_players.name: Justin Herbert
key_players.note: High-volume SF2; matchup-proof unless the Chargers forget he exists again.

key_players.name: Jahmyr Gibbs
key_players.note: Receiving usage remains elite; arrow firmly up in full PPR.

key_players.name: A.J. Brown
key_players.note: Target alpha who erases bad weeks in one quarter.

key_players.name: Travis Kelce
key_players.note: Chiefs WR room is banged up/suspended; he’s the adult in the room (again).

key_players.name: Alvin Kamara
key_players.note: Not peak AK, but still bankable PPR juice.

analysis.bench_potential: Matthew Stafford as a third QB in SF is nasty depth; Jameson Williams’ volatility can win weeks; Jermaine Burton is a stash with spike-week traits.
analysis.make_or_break: RB depth behind Gibbs/Kamara (Swift/Javonte) holding up and Kelce staying healthy. Also, don’t galaxy-brain benching Herbert in SF—lmao why draft two Ferraris to park one?

rankings.summary: CMC + Etienne + Achane with Stroud/Tua is unfair; WR room led by Ja’Marr keeps the ceiling sky-high.

key_players.name: Christian McCaffrey
key_players.note: Still the safest 25-touch profile around.

key_players.name: De’Von Achane
key_players.note: Back healthy and explosive; schemed touches make him a weekly nuke.

key_players.name: Travis Etienne
key_players.note: Three-down role with receiving work keeps the PPR floor plush.

key_players.name: Ja’Marr Chase
key_players.note: Elite alpha; bounce-backs come fast and loud.

key_players.name: C.J. Stroud
key_players.note: MVP-level floor; even with banged-up pass-catchers, he delivers.

key_players.name: Tua Tagovailoa
key_players.note: Stack-friendly and matchup exploitable—ride the hot hand in SF.

analysis.bench_potential: Jared Goff offers safe QB3 starts; Jordan Addison/Jayden Reed/Quentin Johnston can pop—monitor Reed’s short-week health; Tucker Kraft/Pat Freiermuth are playable TE patch-ups.
analysis.make_or_break: Choosing the right QB (Stroud vs Tua) and managing three elite RBs’ start/sit. Also, this much speed should come with a speeding ticket.

rankings.summary: League-best Week 1 scoring and elite depth at QB/WR; RBs are good enough behind Saquon.

key_players.name: Lamar Jackson
key_players.note: Konami code remains intact; weekly 30-point threat.

key_players.name: Saquon Barkley
key_players.note: Eagles offense lifts TD equity even when efficiency dips.

key_players.name: Garrett Wilson
key_players.note: Target hog with after-catch magic.

key_players.name: Jaylen Waddle
key_players.note: Field tilting speed; WR1 weeks in his range often.

key_players.name: Zay Flowers
key_players.note: Second-year leap vibes; designed touches a plus.

key_players.name: Tank Dell
key_players.note: When healthy, he’s a weekly missile in Stroud’s hands.

analysis.bench_potential: Trevor Lawrence as SF depth is luxurious; Jaylen Warren/Brian Robinson are volume plays; Blake Corum is a stash while Kyren dominates early.
analysis.make_or_break: Health for the WR core (Dell especially) and weekly RB2 decisions. Also, collecting WRs like Infinity Stones only works if you actually snap them into the lineup.

rankings.summary: Tyreek + JJ + London with ARich is a juggernaut; record be damned—this is a title build.

key_players.name: Anthony Richardson
key_players.note: Rushing cheat code; pass-game growth boosts weekly ceiling further.

key_players.name: Tyreek Hill
key_players.note: Still breaks scoring systems; matchup-proof.

key_players.name: Justin Jefferson
key_players.note: Alpha usage; even quiet weeks are 15+ in PPR.

key_players.name: Drake London
key_players.note: Target share machine with red-zone upside.

key_players.name: Dalton Kincaid
key_players.note: Route participation + red-zone looks = top-5 TE path.

key_players.name: James Cook
key_players.note: Passing-game usage stabilizes the floor; big-play threat.

analysis.bench_potential: Mark Andrews gives you TE leverage; Aaron Jones steady; Jonathon Brooks/Braelon Allen are patience stashes; Jordan Love/Aaron Rodgers offer startable QB weeks if needed; Xavier Worthy is a hold while the shoulder heals—don’t drop, but don’t force it.
analysis.make_or_break: Keeping ARich healthy and choosing between two elite TEs smartly. Also, drafting two top-five TEs? Bold. Starting both in SF? Bolder. We respect the chaos.

rankings.summary: Josh Allen + Kyren + LaPorta is a filthy spine; if WR2 play settles, this team can win any week.

key_players.name: Josh Allen
key_players.note: QB1 overall profile; rushing TDs still his thing.

key_players.name: Kyren Williams
key_players.note: Workhorse usage confirmed early; TD equity intact.

key_players.name: Sam LaPorta
key_players.note: Target magnet at TE; mismatch every week.

key_players.name: Derrick Henry
key_players.note: Even on a new team, he’s still a hammer—ride the volume.

key_players.name: Marquise Brown
key_players.note: Chiefs’ WR injuries/suspension funnel targets his way.

key_players.name: Terry McLaurin
key_players.note: Perennial 25% target share threat; stable WR2 floor.

analysis.bench_potential: Quinshon Judkins/LeQuint Allen/Damien Martinez are premium dynasty stashes; Bo Nix/Russ Wilson cover byes; Troy Franklin/Jalen McMillan have spike-week profiles.
analysis.make_or_break: Finding weekly WR2 consistency (Diggs’ NE volatility is real). Also, drafting three backs who run like wrecking balls—linebackers are filing HR complaints.

rankings.summary: Hurts + JT with Aiyuk/Nico/Kittle is a steady contender; young WRs add week-winning upside.

key_players.name: Jalen Hurts
key_players.note: Rushing TD cheat; safe top-5 QB.

key_players.name: Jonathan Taylor
key_players.note: Role + goal-line work still elite; Giddens is the handcuff to hold.

key_players.name: Brandon Aiyuk
key_players.note: Hyper-efficient, high-leverage targets.

key_players.name: Nico Collins
key_players.note: Alpha usage with YAC; locked WR1/2.

key_players.name: George Kittle
key_players.note: Volatile weekly, but week-winning spikes remain.

key_players.name: Caleb Williams
key_players.note: SF superflex upside even with rookie volatility; Odunze chemistry building.

analysis.bench_potential: Rome Odunze and Emeka Egbuka bring big-play juice; DJ Giddens/Isaac Guerendo are premium handcuffs; Chase Brown is a sneaky stash; two elite DSTs to stream by matchup.
analysis.make_or_break: Navigating James Conner’s role as Trey Benson pushes for more work. Also, lmao still rostering JuJu in 2025? That’s commitment to the bit.

rankings.summary: Bijan + sun-god + a hall-of-fame WR room; if RB2/QB2 stabilize, this jumps tiers fast.

key_players.name: Bijan Robinson
key_players.note: Receiving eruption in Week 1 reminds everyone why he’s top-3.

key_players.name: Amon-Ra St. Brown
key_players.note: PPR metronome; knee cleaned up, still dominating volume.

key_players.name: Davante Adams
key_players.note: Rams brought him in to score—red-zone maven.

key_players.name: DJ Moore
key_players.note: Target share stays sticky; big plays coming.

key_players.name: Trey McBride
key_players.note: Top-3 usage at TE with elite route rate.

key_players.name: Kyler Murray
key_players.note: Rushing + weapons give a stable 20+ floor.

analysis.bench_potential: Roman Wilson/Tetairoa McMillan could be second-half breakouts; Calvin Ridley has volatility but massive spike weeks; Keaton Mitchell is a stash while usage sorts out.
analysis.make_or_break: Rachaad White’s efficiency and Bryce/Shedeur viability as a QB2 in SF. Also, this WR room is so stacked it should pay luxury tax.

rankings.summary: Win-now QBs plus elite rookies; RB room must hold serve for weekly consistency.

key_players.name: Brock Purdy
key_players.note: System AND talent—high weekly floor.

key_players.name: Geno Smith
key_players.note: Volume + weapons keep him SF-viable.

key_players.name: Malik Nabers
key_players.note: Early target deluge; rookie WR1 path is open.

key_players.name: Brock Bowers
key_players.note: Knee scare minor; usage screams top-3 TE.

key_players.name: DK Metcalf
key_players.note: Touchdown swings decide WR1/2 outcomes weekly.

key_players.name: Tony Pollard
key_players.note: New scheme, but passing-down role preserves PPR value.

analysis.bench_potential: Jaxon Smith-Njigba’s usage is rising; Phil Mafah/Dylan Sampson are ‘next man up’ types; Ricky Pearsall is a real-life good WR who’ll stack spike weeks; Jordan Mason worth monitoring.
analysis.make_or_break: Pollard/Mafah/Hubbard trio producing enough until a true RB2 emerges—and Nabers’ production staying QB-proof. This roster screams dynasty…or an NIL collective.

rankings.summary: Breece + Burrow/Fields with Pitts/Engram can rip off a streak; needs a second WR to stick.

key_players.name: Breece Hall
key_players.note: Workhorse with chunk plays; PPR monster.

key_players.name: Joe Burrow
key_players.note: Health and OL cooperate? Top-6 outcome still in play.

key_players.name: Justin Fields
key_players.note: Konami QB in SF; fantasy goodness even when messy.

key_players.name: Ladd McConkey
key_players.note: Day-one separator; should live in the 6–9 target range.

key_players.name: Mike Evans
key_players.note: Still that dude in the red zone.

key_players.name: Kyle Pitts
key_players.note: Route volume is there—QB connection decides the rest.

analysis.bench_potential: Khalil Shakir is a weekly flex candidate; Tyjae Spears offers pass-game PPR value; Bucky Irving/Jaylen Wright are bench stashes (Wright working back from early-week absence); Omarion Hampton is the long view.
analysis.make_or_break: Burrow bouncing back to elite and Pitts finally converting air yards. Also, rostering Isaac TeSlaa is either 4D chess or you just like cool names—lmao.

rankings.summary: 2-0 start, but Mixon’s multi-week absence caps ceiling; Puka + Hock + Jacobs can carry.

key_players.name: Puka Nacua
key_players.note: Target magnet; even bandaged up he eats.

key_players.name: T.J. Hockenson
key_players.note: Back to heavy usage; high PPR floor at TE.

key_players.name: Josh Jacobs
key_players.note: Lead role in GB keeps the weekly RB2 floor steady.

key_players.name: Keon Coleman
key_players.note: Contested-catch ace tied to a big-armed QB—spike weeks incoming.

key_players.name: George Pickens
key_players.note: Air-yards god with YAC pop; volatile but fun.

key_players.name: Baker Mayfield
key_players.note: Serviceable QB2 while JJ McCarthy ramps up.

analysis.bench_potential: Ashton Jeanty is a premium dynasty stash who could matter sooner than later; Christian Watson boom/bust flex; Jaleel McLaughlin/J.K. Dobbins are speculative bets.
analysis.make_or_break: Surviving Joe Mixon’s at-least-four-game absence and finding weekly QB points. Your RB room is giving ‘history channel’ vibes—cool story, needs some present-day juice.

rankings.summary: Youth wave with real upside (MHJ, Daniels, Benson). It’ll be bumpy early but dangerous late.

key_players.name: Marvin Harrison Jr.
key_players.note: Already playing like a vet WR1; weekly must-start.

key_players.name: Jayden Daniels
key_players.note: Dual-threat floor; fantasy-friendly even in losses.

key_players.name: Trey Benson
key_players.note: Flashed big plays and is pushing for more work over Conner.

key_players.name: Isiah Pacheco
key_players.note: Locked-in touches on a good offense; RB2 rock.

key_players.name: Jake Ferguson
key_players.note: Red-zone weapon with steady routes.

key_players.name: Zach Charbonnet
key_players.note: RB2/FLEX with contingent top-15 upside.

analysis.bench_potential: Penix can stream in good matchups; Luther Burden/Luke McCaffrey/Xavier Legette are breakout watchlist; Cade Stover/Terrance Ferguson give TE depth.
analysis.make_or_break: How fast the rookies level up, and whether Benson’s role keeps growing. Drafting half the 2025 class is brave—now let the kids cook.

rankings.summary: Dak–CeeDee–Olave can hang, but Rice’s suspension and shaky RB2 play dragged Week 1. Needs a spark.

key_players.name: Dak Prescott
key_players.note: High weekly floor; stackable with CeeDee.

key_players.name: CeeDee Lamb
key_players.note: Target hog; weekly top-5 WR upside.

key_players.name: Chris Olave
key_players.note: Route-god with volume—QB play determines the ceiling.

key_players.name: Kenneth Walker
key_players.note: Talent undeniable; offense needs to cooperate.

key_players.name: Dallas Goedert
key_players.note: Reliable TE floor with occasional spikes.

key_players.name: Brian Thomas Jr.
key_players.note: Big-play rookie who can swing weeks on 3 targets.

analysis.bench_potential: Rashee Rice returns Week 7—stash through the suspension; Drake Maye is a long-view SF stash; Josh Downs is a PPR band-aid; Tank Bigsby is purely contingent now.
analysis.make_or_break: Finding an every-week RB2 (Ekeler’s new situation helps, but watch usage) and surviving until Rice returns. Bench looks like a taxi squad that missed its Uber—lmao.
